=== Second cedi ===
The first issue of banknotes, dated 1967, was in denominations of âµ1, âµ5 and âµ10. A second series, introduced in 1972 and 1973, consisted of âµ1, âµ2, âµ5 and âµ10 notes. The 1979 series, for which old notes were exchanged at a reduced rate (see above) consisted of âµ1, âµ2, âµ5, âµ10, âµ20 and âµ50 banknotes.
In 1983, a new banknote series was introduced in denominations of âµ10, âµ20, âµ50, âµ100 and âµ200 cedis. Higher denomination banknotes were later introduced: âµ500 (1986), âµ1000 (1991), âµ2000 (1995), âµ5000 (1996), âµ10,000 and âµ20,000 (2002). In 2005, banknotes in circulation were âµ1000, âµ2000, âµ5000, âµ10,000 and âµ20,000.
