=== Third cedi ===
The new currency is denominated in Ghana cedi ('''GHâµ'''), a unit equal to 10,000 old cedi, and Ghana pesewa ('''Gp'''), equal to one-hundredth of a Ghana cedi or 10,000 old pesewa (100 old cedi). Banknotes are issued in GHâµ1, GHâµ5, GHâµ10, GHâµ20, and GHâµ50 denominations. Old currency were withdrawn beginning in July 2007, and after a six month transition may only be exchanged at banks and will no longer be [[legal tender]]. The Bank of Ghana has launched a [http://www.ghanacedi.gov.gh website on this re-denomination campaign]. A new GHâµ2 Cedi banknote was issued on May 14, 2010 to meet public need for an intermediary denomination and reduce the frequency, and associated cost, of printing large volumes of the GHâµ1 banknote. The introduction of the new denomination coincides with the conclusion of the year-long centenary celebrations of the birth of Dr. Kwame Nkrumah, Ghanaâs first president, and has the commemorative text âCENTENARY OF THE BIRTH OF DR. KWAME NKRUMAHâ.<ref>[http://banknotenews.com/files/b31af730a7ecef40fe266eeec228aa2b-1069.php Ghana new 2-cedi note confirmed] BanknoteNews.com. Retrieved 2011-10-20.</ref>
